20company%20must%20%26quot%3Bcontinuously%20raise%20our%20own%20bar.%26quot%3B%3Cp%3EAdam%20Gray%2FBloomberg%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3ERobinhood's%20CEO%20says%20business%20is%20thriving%20and%20it's%20cutting%20jobs%20to%20%26quot%3Bmaximize%20our%20talent%20density.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%26quot%3BOur%20ambitions%20require%20us%20to%20continuously%20raise%20our%20own%20bar%2C%26quot%3B%20Vlad%20Tenev%20wrote%20in%20a%20layoff%20memo.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20trading%20platform%20isn't%20the%20only%20company%20that's%20drawn%20connections%20between%20worker%20performance%20and%20cuts.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3ERobinhood%20has%20a%20message%20for%20workers%20losing%20their%20jobs%3A%20The%20company%20isn't%20struggling.%20You%20are.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat's%20the%20crux%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frobinhood-layoffs-job-cuts-memo-ceo-vlad-tenev-2026-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ETuesday's%20layoff%20memo%3C%2Fa%3E%20from%20the%20CEO%20of%20the%20trading%20platform.%20It's%20the%20latest%20example%20of%20a%20high-profile%20company%20trimming%20head%20count%20while%20simultaneously%20saying%20it's%20doing%20well.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BRobinhood's%20business%20has%20never%20been%20stronger%2C%26quot%3B%20wrote%20Vlad%20Tenev%20while%20announcing%20plans%20to%20reduce%2010%25%20of%20the%20company's%20workforce.%20Robinhood%20had%202%2C900%20full-time%20employees%20at%20the%20end%20of%202025%2C%20according%20to%20a%20February%20securities%20filing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETenev%20didn't%20explicitly%20call%20the%20%26quot%3BRobinhoodies%26quot%3B%20being%20let%20go%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmeta-performance-cuts-mark-zuckerberg-memo%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Elow%20performers%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20as%20Meta%20CEO%20Mark%20Zuckerberg%20did%20of%20staff%20booted%20from%20his%20Facebook%20parent%20last%20year.%20Tenev%20did%2C%20though%2C%20draw%20a%20clear%20contrast%20between%20the%20workforce%20Robinhood%20is%20shedding%20and%20the%20one%20it%20wants%20to%20keep.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BOur%20execution%20is%20strong%20today%2C%20but%20our%20ambitions%20require%20us%20to%20continuously%20raise%20our%20own%20bar%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20wrote%2C%20while%20saying%20he%20was%20grateful%20to%20those%20departing.%20%26quot%3BThe%20goal%20is%20to%20maximize%20our%20talent%20density.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnthony%20Klotz%2C%20a%20professor%20at%20the%20University%20College%20London%20School%20of%20Management%2C%20said%20the%20memo's%20subtext%20is%20clear%3A%20%26quot%3BThis%20was%20a%20performance-based%20decision.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2244658075-b708-4c3e-b714-86a6af1fc14b%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3E'No%20job%20is%20100%25%20secure'%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ETenev's%20statement%20illustrates%20how%20the%20rationale%20for%20layoffs%20has%20evolved%20in%20recent%20years.%20Instead%20of%20citing%20weak%20business%20conditions%2C%20some%20executives%20are%20arguing%20that%20cuts%20are%20necessary%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmiddle-managers-have-more-direct-reports-after-great-flattening-2026-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ecreate%20leaner%20organizations%3C%2Fa%3E%20staffed%20by%20fewer%2C%20higher-performing%20employees.%20For%20workers%20losing%20their%20jobs%2C%20though%2C%20the%20distinction%20may%20offer%20little%20comfort.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20overarching%20message%20for%20everybody%20is%20that%20no%20job%20is%20100%25%20secure%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Lee%20Harding%2C%20a%20recruiter%20for%20a%20global%20search%20firm.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20those%20at%20Robinhood%20in%20particular%2C%20he%20expects%20the%20takeaway%20to%20also%20be%20personal%3A%20If%20he%20were%20among%20those%20let%20go%2C%20he%20said%20he'd%20interpret%20Tenev's%20message%20as%20meaning%20%26quot%3BI'm%20not%20good%20enough.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERobinhood%20declined%20to%20comment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20securities%20filing%20Tuesday%2C%20Robinhood%20said%20the%20cuts%20come%20as%20June's%20month-to-date%20average%20daily%20trading%20volumes%20hit%20record%20levels%20across%20equities%2C%20options%2C%20and%20prediction%20markets.%20That%20follows%20the%20company's%20April%20report%20that%20first-quarter%20cryptocurrency%20revenue%20dropped%2047%25%20year%20over%20year%20to%20%24134%20million%2C%20reflecting%20weaker%20retail%20trading%20amid%20a%20slump%20in%20crypto%20markets.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2297770acc-2424-48f5-aa4c-6b7704f69e83%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EOperating%20lean%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EMicrosoft%2C%20Block%2C%20and%20several%20other%20employers%20have%20also%20described%20their%20businesses%20as%20robust%20while%20conducting%20layoffs.%20Some%20have%20cited%20AI%20as%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Flist-companies-replacing-human-employees-with-ai-layoffs-workforce-reductions%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ereason%20for%20job%20cuts%3C%2Fa%3E%20while%20also%20encouraging%20still-employed%20workers%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fceos-cite-ai-for-job-cuts-while-urging-worker-adoption-2026-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eembrace%20the%20technology%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20common%20thread%20in%20recent%20layoff%20memos%20is%20a%20desire%20to%20cut%20down%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwelcome-to-the-age-of-the-corporate-megamanager-2026-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emiddle-management%20layers%3C%2Fa%3E.%20The%20change%20reflects%20lessons%20from%20companies'%20overhiring%20during%20the%20pandemic%2C%20AI's%20automation%20capabilities%2C%20and%20economic%20uncertainty%2C%20said%20Melissa%20Swift%2C%20founder%20and%20CEO%20of%20organizational%20consultancy%20Anthrome%20Insight.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhen%20you%20operate%20lean%2C%20you%20can%20pivo