20Dutch%20to%20him%20at%20our%20home%20in%20the%20US.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20I%20first%20matched%20with%20my%20now-husband%20on%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftinder-married-met-husband-online-dating-2019-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Edating%20app%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20his%20profile%20said%20he%20was%20from%20Belgium.%20At%20the%20time%2C%20I%20assumed%20he%20spoke%20French.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20had%20been%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Flive-part-time-mexico-good-health-benefits-2026-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Estudying%20Spanish%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20a%20few%20years%2C%20and%20in%20the%20language-learning%20community%2C%20there%20is%20a%20joke%20that%20the%20best%20way%20to%20learn%20a%20language%20is%20to%20date%20someone%20who%20speaks%20it.%20I%20had%20fleeting%20thoughts%20that%20I%20would%20finally%20be%20able%20to%20pronounce%20the%20names%20of%20high-end%20French%20fashion%20brands.%20Before%20our%20first%20date%2C%20I%20realized%20he%20was%20actually%20from%20the%20Dutch-speaking%20part%20of%20Belgium%2C%20and%20I%20remember%20thinking%2C%20%26quot%3BWho%20would%20want%20to%20learn%20Dutch%3F%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20our%20relationship%20progressed%20and%20things%20became%20more%20serious%2C%20I%20asked%20my%20future%20husband%20if%20he%20thought%20I%20should%20learn%20Dutch.%20His%20answer%20was%20honest%2C%20%26quot%3BIt's%20not%20very%20useful.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDutch%20is%20primarily%20spoken%20in%20the%20Netherlands%20and%20the%20Flanders%20region%20of%20Belgium%2C%20where%20my%20husband%20is%20from.%20Most%20Dutch%20speakers%20also%20speak%20English%2C%20so%20as%20an%20English%20speaker%2C%20learning%20Dutch%20isn't%20all%20that%20necessary.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20eventually%20started%20talking%20about%20moving%20in%20together%2C%20getting%20married%2C%20and%20having%20a%20family%20one%20day.%20I%20asked%20my%20husband%20if%20it%20was%20important%20to%20him%20that%20his%20child%20speak%20his%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fraised-bilingual-grateful-family-communication-2023-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Enative%20language%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Without%20hesitation%2C%20he%20answered%20that%20it%20was.%20It%20was%20then%20that%20I%20knew%20that%20if%20our%20yet-to-be-conceived%20child%20was%20going%20to%20speak%20Dutch%2C%20their%20American%20mother%20would%20be%20the%20weak%20link%20if%20I%20didn't%20learn%20the%20language%2C%20too.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221600%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22The%20author%20with%20her%20husband%20and%20their%20son%20while%20at%20a%20pub.%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6a315ac7e826bfa433d6e678%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20author%20said%20her%20husband%20mentioned%20he%20would%20like%20his%20future%20children%20to%20speak%20Dutch%20before%20they%20got%20married.%20It%20was%20then%20that%20she%20knew%20that%20she%20wanted%20to%20learn%20the%20language%2C%20too.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20Renate%20Flanagen.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%224141f43e-582b-4937-ae7c-6a05bd9c9772%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EHis%20family%20has%20been%20encouraging%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EShortly%20after%20I%20moved%20in%20with%20my%20now-husband%2C%20I%20started%20studying%20Dutch.%20I%20used%20a%20l%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Freference%2Ffree-language-learning-apps%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eanguage-learning%20app%3C%2Fa%3E%20with%20him%20by%20my%20side%2C%20coaching%20me%20on%20pronunciation%20and%20grammar.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMost%20Dutch%20language-learning%20resources%20I've%20found%20are%20based%20on%20Dutch%20spoken%20in%20the%20Netherlands.%20Dutch%20in%20the%20Netherlands%20and%20Dutch%20in%20Belgium%20are%20akin%20to%20English%20spoken%20in%20England%20compared%20to%20English%20in%20the%20United%20States.%20The%20pronunciation%20and%20meanings%20of%20some%20of%20the%20words%20differ.%20For%20instance%2C%20%26quot%3Blopen%26quot%3B%20in%20the%20Netherlands%20means%20%26quot%3Bto%20walk%2C%26quot%3B%20while%20in%20Belgium%2C%20it%20means%20%26quot%3Bto%20run.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI've%20been%20fortunate%20that%20my%20efforts%20to%20learn%20Dutch%20have%20been%20met%20with%20enthusiasm%20and%20encouragement%20from%20my%20husband's%20family%20and%20friends.%20Because%20it's%20uncommon%20for%20Americans%20to%20learn%20the%20language%2C%20the%20expectations%20are%20comically%20low.%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EOn%20my%20first%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fexpectations-first-london-brussels-visit-turned-out-to-be-wrong-2023-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Evisit%20to%20Belgium%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20my%20Dutch%20was%20still%20at%20a%20basic%20level.%20My%20vocabulary%20was%20limited%2C%20and%20I%20could%20only%20speak%20in%20the%20present%20tense.%20Even%20so%2C%20my%20husband's%20friends%20joked%20that%20I%20would%20make%20a%20good%20%26quot%3Bbuitenlander%2C%26quot%3B%20meaning%20a%20foreigner%2C%20because%20I%20spoke%20more%20Dutch%20than%20some%20people%20who%20had%20moved%20to%20Belgium%20and%20had%20lived%20there%20for%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22aedf8e3e-8968-40df-a9a8-46301279795e%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3ESeeing%20my%20son%20speak%20Dutch%20is%20the%20greatest%20reward%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20husband%20and%20I%20now%20have%20a%202-year-old%20son%20that%20we're%20raising%20in%20the%20United%20States.%20One%20of%20my%20greatest%20fears%20of%20being%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhigher-cost-of-living-creating-multigenerational-homes-2026-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Emulticultural%20family%3C%2Fa%3E%20living%20in%20the%20US%20was%20that%20my%20son%20wouldn't%20have%20any%20connection%20to%20his%20dad's%20culture.%20Even%20though%20my%20Dutch%20is%20at%20an%20elementary%20level%2C%20my%20husband%20and%20I%20primarily%20speak%20Dutch%20with%20our%20son.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22The%20author%20and%20her%20son%20while%20on%20a%20trip%20to%20Belgium.%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6a315b36e826bfa433d6e682%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22900%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20author%20said%20her%20son%20spoke%20Dutch%20with%20a%20cousin%20while%20they%20were%20visiting.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20Renate%20Flanagen.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EDuring%20a%20recent%20visit%20from%20my%20husband's%20family%2C%20my%20son%20got%20to%20play%20with%20his%202-year-old%20cousin%20from%20Belgium%2C%20who%20only%20speaks%20Dutch.%20It%20made%20my%20heart%20swell%20to%20watch%20my%20son%20and%20his%20cousin%20play%20%26quot%3Bkeuken%2C%26quot%3B%20meaning%20kitchen.%20My%20son%20pretended%20to%20make%20soup%20in%20an%20empty%20cooking%20pot%20and%20offered%20a%20%26quot%3Blepel%26quot%3B%20(spoon)%20for%20his%20cousin%20to%20pretend%20to%20drink%20from.%20He%20asked%20his%20cousin%2C%20%26quot%3Bwat%20denk%20je%3F%26quot%3B%20meaning%20%26quot%3Bwhat%20do%20you%20think%3F%26quot%3B%20to%20which%20she%20responded%2C%20%26quot%3Blekker!%26quot%3B%20meaning%20%26quot%3Btasty%2C%26quot%3B%20and%20they%20laughed%20hysterically.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBy%20learning%20Dutch%2C%20I'm%20honoring%20my%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrailing-spouse-moved-europe-philippines-husband-acting-writing-regrets-2026-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ehusband's%20culture%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20language%20so%20that%20our%20son%20can%20grow%20up%20as%20a%20Belgian%20American%2C%20no%20matter%20where%20we%20live.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famerican-mom-learned-dutch-so-child-could-connect-belgian-roots-2026-6%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1781630041000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.